name: heat production, wood pellet, at furnace 9kW | heat, central or small-scale, other than natural gas | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3581/documentation

Activity represents combustion of wood pellets in average small wood pellet furnaces in Switzerland in 2014. Only uncertainty factors were adjusted in order to provide a GLO activity. The inventory shall be considered valid for boilers with nominal capacities in the approximate range of 5 to 20 kW. The activity represents average annual operation including start/stop (warm up and cool down), which reduces the efficiency compared to rated values provided by boiler manufacturers and increases some emission factors such as CO. Air emission factors as well as other exchanges correspond to v2.2 except of PM, CO, NOx, CH4 and NMVOC. These key emission factors were updated based on latest available information.

From reception of wood pellets.

This activity describes the combustion of wood pellets until heat production at the boiler outlet. Included are the infrastructure, the wood requirements (average pellets, u=10%), the emissions to air, the electricity needed for operation, and the disposal of the ashes.
